<html>
<body>

<h1>What Can JavaScript Do?</h1>

<p>JavaScript can change HTML attributes.</p>

<p>In this case JavaScript changes the src (source) attribute of an image.</p>

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='bulb2.jpg'">Turn on the light</button>

<img id="myImage" src="bulb.jpg" style="width:100px">

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='bulb.jpg'">Turn off the light</button>
<h1>What Can JavaScript Do?</h1>

<p id="demo">JavaScript can change the style of an HTML element.</p>

<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo').style.fontSize='35px'">Click Me!</button>

<p id="demo">JavaScript can hide HTML elements.</p>

<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo').style.display='none'">Click Me!</button>
<p id="demo" style="display:none">Hello JavaScript!</p>

<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo').style.display='block'">Click Me!</button>
</body>
